Shops relocated to decongest Delhi Airport.
New Delhi, Aug 1 (PTI) Shops at the domestic terminal of Delhi airport have been relocated to provide additional space for seamless passenger movement, the government said today. A Public Accounts Committee headed by Congress leader K V Thomas had in its draft report indicted the Delhi airport operator about shrinkage of space for passengers because of restaurants, retail outlets, duty-free complexes and executive lounges. The Committee had said that this could hamper passenger movement incase of a mishap. 